# Card-audit (mtg-948 Part B): Paralyze — Aura ETB taps enchanted creature (scripted).
#
# Closed issue mtg-529 closed Paralyze as WORKING but carried NO scripted puzzle
# with semantic assertions. This audit puzzle SCRIPTS casting the Aura onto an
# opponent's creature and asserts the enter-the-battlefield tap trigger fires.
#
# Paralyze is a {B} Enchantment — Aura "Enchant creature": "When Paralyze enters,
# tap enchanted creature." (K:Enchant:Creature; T:Mode$ ChangesZone | Destination$
# Battlefield | ValidCard$ Card.Self | Execute$ TrigTap; SVar:TrigTap:DB$ Tap |
# Defined$ Enchanted). The ETB trigger taps the creature it is attached to (CR
# 303.4, 603). It also imposes a "doesn't untap" replacement, but this puzzle
# asserts the immediate, observable ETB-tap trigger.
#
# Aspects exercised (issue mtg-529):
#   1. Parses + castable as a {B} Aura that attaches to a creature (spell cast).
#   2. The Aura resolves onto the battlefield ATTACHED to the chosen creature
#      (battlefield membership).
#   3. The ETB "tap enchanted creature" trigger FIRES on entry (trigger fired
#      from Paralyze).
#
# Scenario:
#   - P0: Paralyze in hand, 1 Swamp to pay {B}.
#   - P1: an untapped Grizzly Bears (2/2) it controls.
#   - Script: P0 casts Paralyze enchanting the Grizzly Bears; the ETB trigger
#     taps it.

[metadata]
Name:Card Audit - Paralyze Taps on ETB
Goal:Win
Turns:1
Difficulty:Easy
Description:P0 scripts Paralyze ({B} Aura) onto P1's Grizzly Bears. The Aura resolves attached to the Bears and its enter-the-battlefield trigger taps the enchanted creature. Backs issue mtg-529 (Enchant creature + ChangesZone->Battlefield DB$ Tap Defined$ Enchanted; CR 303.4).

[state]
turn=1
activeplayer=p0
activephase=MAIN1
p0life=20
p0hand=Paralyze
p0battlefield=Swamp
p0library=Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp;Swamp

p1life=20
p1battlefield=Grizzly Bears
p1library=Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest;Forest

[p0_script]
# Cast Paralyze enchanting P1's Grizzly Bears (the only creature on board, so the
# enchant target is unambiguous). Then PASS for the rest of the game so the board
# stays frozen and the membership assertions stay durable.
cast Paralyze targeting Grizzly Bears
PASS_UNTIL turn=5,phase=MAIN1

[p1_script]
# P1 takes no proactive action (the tapped, locked-down Bears cannot attack).
PASS_UNTIL turn=5,phase=MAIN1

[assertions]
# The Aura was actually cast.
spell cast Paralyze
# Its enter-the-battlefield "tap enchanted creature" trigger fired on entry.
trigger fired from Paralyze
# The Aura resolved onto the battlefield (it is now a permanent P0 controls).
battlefield contains Paralyze
# The enchanted creature is still on the board (Paralyze TAPS, it does not
# destroy): P1 still controls the Grizzly Bears.
opponent battlefield contains Grizzly Bears
